    "body": "This PR is a follow-up from: https://github.com/triton-lang/triton/pull/10215, since async commit group is removed, TDM ops can no longer take advantage of this as a counter barrier when combining redundant wait ops.\r\n\r\nThis PR generalize combineRedundantWaitOps into a callback-based API that works with any wait/barrier op pair, not just ttg.async_wait/async_commit_group. Use this to fold consecutive amdgpu.async_tdm_wait ops into a single wait taking all operand tokens and the minimum wait count.\r\n\r\nAlso add TDMOpInterface, a common interface for AMD TDM data-movement ops (`async_tdm_copy_global_to_local`, `async_tdm_copy_local_to_global`, `async_tdm_scatter`, `async_tdm_gather`). Those ops are used as the counter barrier when combining TDM waits.",
    "created_at": "2026-05-05T13:09:43Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-05-06T00:55:54Z",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-06T00:55:51Z",
